Sorry, sometimes I forget that I have BoBC and Epic and think that is the average mage. I remember the old days of having to use regular pets and nuke with mana hehe. However to be fair to me, you have to understand that the circle of people that I raid with makes me feel very much below average. I look around and all the mages that are at my level in terms of &quot;raiding&quot; have vastly superior gear. I am talking Shield of Auras, Creater Dagger ect....<br>
<br>
Also a ton of mages have epics now. It isn't as rare as it once was. It is still hard to get but alot of people have them. Seems everywhere i turn there is a mage epic now.  I just think we need to be careful not to ask for to much. We are not druids and are not loved like them. They get to have it all without giving up anything. For the rest of us it doesn't work this way. If we improve to much in healing we will be forced to give up something and I for one don't want to give up anymore.<br>
